column2: Q1_"Never tell anyone the real reason you did something unless it is useful to do so."
column3: Q2_"The best way to handle people is to tell them what they want to hear."
column4: Q3_"One should take action only when sure it is morally right."
column5: Q4_"Most people are basically good and kind."
column6: Q5_"It is safest to assume that all people have a vicious streak and it will come out when they are given a chance."
column7: Q6_"Honesty is the best policy in all cases."
column8: Q7_"There is no excuse for lying to someone else."
column9: Q8_"Generally speaking, people won't work hard unless they're forced to do so."
column10: Q9_"All in all, it is better to be humble and honest than to be important and dishonest."
column11: Q10_"When you ask someone to do something for you, it is best to give the real reasons for wanting it rather than giving reasons which carry more weight."
column12: Q11_"Most people who get ahead in the world lead clean, moral lives."
column13: Q12_"Anyone who completely trusts anyone else is asking for trouble."
column14: Q13_"The biggest difference between most criminals and other people is that the criminals are stupid enough to get caught."
column16: Q15_"It is wise to flatter important people."
column17: Q16_"It is possible to be good in all respects."
column18: Q17_"P.T. Barnum was wrong when he said that there's a sucker born every minute."
column19: Q18_"It is hard to get ahead without cutting corners here and there."
column20: Q19_"People suffering from incurable diseases should have the choice of being put painlessly to death."
column21: Q20_"Most people forget more easily the death of their parents than the loss of their property."
